<p><strong>Postdoctoral  position at CIAE - DEMRE, Universidad de Chile.</strong><p></p>
  Two new  postdoctoral positions are being offered at the Center for Advanced Research in  Education (CIAE) in a joint Research Unit with the Department for Educational  Assessment (DEMRE), both at the Universidad de Chile.<p></p>
  Candidates  should exhibit evidence of outstanding research results and should have  received a PhD in Statistics, Psychometrics, Assessment or related fields by  the beginning of the appointment and not before 2010. The position is for  full-time research activity, with no teaching duties, and with expected  participation in conferences or workshops in Chile or abroad. The preparation  of the candidates and their interests should enable them to contribute to  developing the research agenda of DEMRE, including studies to improve  assessment instruments currently in use as well as the design of new assessment  instruments and studies that use the large accumulation of historical data  available in DEMRE, to support and inform national educational policy. Positions  are for one year, renewable for the same period up to three years. Selected  postdocs will be evaluated at the end of each period according to the CIAE  excellence standards.<p></p>
  CIAE will  cover flight tickets, and will pay a monthly salary of around US$2,250 as well  as paying for outreach related costs, subject to evaluation. Nevertheless,  selected postdocs are expected to apply for national grants and research  funding. Spanish language is not required.<p></p>
  Appointments  have no fixed starting date, but should preferably start no later than March  2016. The application process will be open until <strong>March 31, 2016</strong>.<strong> </strong><p></p>
  After completing the application form you will receive a confirmation email with a link that you must send  to the people who will write your recommendation letters.
  <p></p>
Applications  for which three recommendations are not received by the application deadline  will be declared abandoned.</p>
